com.conceptwave.scripting
Class DataObjectList

com.conceptwave.scripting.Object
  com.conceptwave.scripting.CWScriptable
      com.conceptwave.scripting.DataObjectList

public class DataObjectList
extends CWScriptable

Data object list class. The instances of these class contain list of data objects, i.e documents or data structures. It supports access to contents directly by index: dataObjectList[i] to update: dataObjectList[i] = object to remove: dataObjectList.remove(i) to insert: dataObjectList.add(index, object)

Deprecated. As of 5.1. Use add(index, object)

Adds a document to the data object list after a given 'previous' document from the list. If the given document is null or not found, the new document is added at the beginning of the list.

Parameters:
previous - Document from the list or null
objectToAdd - New object to be added to the list.
Returns:
The previous object if there is no duplication, or the duplicated element from the list if the duplication is not allowed.

clearFilter

public void clearFilter(com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean clear)
Set if filter criteria on the table element is to be cleared. NOTE if the table element is part of a finder user interface, the finder's clearFilter must be called. This method should only be called if the table element is in a top level user interface form. Initial value of this flag is set to true. Once the value is sent, it will be set to false. When the filter criteria is cleared, a fetch for the original data will occur.

aList - A data object list which content will be added at the end of this list.

removeAfter

public CwObject removeAfter(CwObject previous)
Deprecated. As of 5.1 use the API delete(index)

Removes a document from the data object list after a specified (previous) document. If the previous document is null or not found the first object of the list is removed. If previous document is not null it must specify an object from the list. In that case the object following it is removed.

Parameters:
previous - Object from the list or null.
Returns:
The removed document or null if the previous object is the last object in the list

sort

public DataObjectList sort(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object comparator)
Sorts the contents of this list. Operation NOT valid with finder results.

Parameters:
comparator - Global script name. Comparator script MUST have two parameters which are the same type as the objects in this list and whose values will be elements from this list. Comparator script MUST return an Integer value. Return value of -1 means parameter 1 is "less" than parameter 2. Return value of 1 means parameter 1 is "greater" than parameter 2. Return value of 0 means parameter 1 is "equal" to parameter 2. If the comparator script name is NULL or not specified, than the default sorting will be alphabetical ascending based on the Data Object ID value for each element.
Returns:
DataObjectList This list sorted.

toArray

public Array toArray()
Deprecated. As of 5.1 data object list supports access to contents directly by index: dataObjectList[i] updated: dataObjectList[i] = object; removed dataObjectList.remove(i) or inserted: add(index, object)

Converts the data object list into array of data objects. The array should be considered read only. Deleting and inserting objects in it will corrupt the data object list.

Returns:
Array of data objects (documents) in the order they are in the data object list.

public String toXML()

Returns:
XML string representing the object list. Empty list returns null.
